The paper deals with the analysis and estimation of the empirical price of anarchy in auctions, which is a topic in game theory and mechanism design. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses techniques based on inferring properties of auctions, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses the rate of error decreasing with the number of auctions and agents, which involves statistical learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the efficiency of auctions, which involves information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category.
